Service Cloud
Attach Records to Chat Transcripts

Search for or create records to attach to a chat transcript as you chat with customers in a Salesforce console app.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To search for and view a record:
Read on the object
Create on Live Chat Transcripts
To create a new record:
Create on the object
Create on Live Chat Transcripts
To edit a record:
Edit on the object
Create on Live Chat Transcripts
To delete a record:
Delete on the object
Create on Live Chat Transcripts

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement. Migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before February 14, 2026.

Find existing records or create new ones to associate with a transcript as you chat with customers. You can attach standard or custom records to your chat transcripts.

While chatting with a customer, click  to attach a record to the transcript.
To search for an existing record:
Click the search icon and type the name of the record and hit ENTER.
Select the check box next to the record you searched for to link it to the chat transcript.
To create a new record:
Click the create icon and complete the information in the new record and save it.

The records you linked are now attached to the transcript. You can access them from the transcriptâ€™s detail view.
title: Attach Records to Chat Transcripts in Salesforce
